JavaScript Modularization Rules:

Never put multiple functions in a single JavaScript file
Create separate .js files for each function or logical component
Use descriptive filenames that match the function purpose
Store JavaScript modules in resources/js/modules/ directory
Import functions using ES6 import/export syntax
In Laravel Blade templates, include JavaScript modules using @vite directive
Example structure:
resources/js/modules/userValidation.js
resources/js/modules/formHandler.js
resources/js/modules/apiClient.js